Louis Joseph Maria Beel (12 April 1902 â€“ 11 February 1977) was a Dutch politician of the defunct Catholic People's Party (KVP) now merged into the Christian Democratic Appeal (CDA). He served as Prime Minister of the Netherlands from 3 July 1946 until 7 August 1948, and again from 22 December 1958 until 19 May 1959. Because of his long service record he was considered by some as having the status of a statesman.
On 22 November 1956, he was granted the honorary title of Minister of State.
